  if (deploymentType === 'databricks' && deploymentStatus?.progress) {
    return <DatabricksProgress progress={deploymentStatus.progress} />;
  }

  // Fallback to existing progress indicator
  return (
    <div className="mt-3 space-y-2">
      {/* ... existing implementation */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Success Criteria:
- [ ] Detailed progress messages for each deployment phase
- [ ] Visual progress indicators show current step
- [ ] Progress bar reflects actual completion percentage
- [ ] Real-time updates as job progresses

---

## Phase 4: Testing & Validation

### Overview
Comprehensive testing to ensure async deployment works reliably.

### Testing Strategy

#### 1. Unit Tests
- Job manager operations (create, update, cleanup)
- Worker phase progression and error handling
- Status endpoint response formatting
- Progress calculation accuracy

#### 2. Integration Tests  
- End-to-end async deployment flow
- Concurrent deployment handling
- Job recovery after server restart
- Frontend polling integration

#### 3. Manual Testing
1. **Start deployment** - verify immediate response
2. **Monitor progress** - check real-time updates
3. **Error handling** - test failure scenarios
4. **Concurrent deployments** - multiple users
5. **Status accuracy** - verify final deployment state

### Performance Considerations

#### Memory Management
- Jobs cleaned up after completion (1 hour retention)
- Limited job data storage (metadata only)
- Automatic cleanup prevents memory leaks

#### Concurrency
- Background jobs run independently
- No shared state between deployments
- Database connections properly pooled

#### Monitoring
- Comprehensive logging for all phases
- Job metrics via health endpoint
- Error tracking and alerting

### Rollout Strategy

#### Feature Flag Ready
- Can disable async behavior via environment variable
- Fallback to synchronous deployment if needed
- Gradual rollout to production users

#### Backward Compatibility
- Existing deployment contracts maintained
- Frontend handles both sync and async responses
- Database schema unchanged

### Success Criteria

#### Automated Tests
- [ ] All unit tests pass
- [ ] Integration tests verify end-to-end flow
- [ ] Performance tests show acceptable memory usage
- [ ] Concurrent deployment tests pass

#### Manual Verification
- [ ] User gets immediate response when starting deployment
- [ ] Real-time progress updates work correctly
- [ ] Error states are handled gracefully
- [ ] Final deployment status is accurate
- [ ] Multiple concurrent deployments work
- [ ] Job cleanup prevents memory buildup

---

## Migration Notes

### No Breaking Changes
- API endpoints maintain same response format
- Frontend components handle both sync/async modes
- Database schema unchanged
- Existing deployments continue working

### Configuration
- No new environment variables required (optional feature flag)
- Uses existing Databricks credentials
- Job retention configurable via environment

### Monitoring
- New job status endpoints for debugging
- Enhanced logging for deployment phases  
- Health check includes job metrics

